   The U.S. District Court for the Northern District of Ohio allows
   attorneys in civil cases to file and retrieve documents from any
   location over the Internet using the Courts Case Management /
   Electronic Case Files (CM/ECF) docketing system. This district is a
   leader in the development and use of electronic filing and is proud to
   have been the first Court to accept an electronic filing over the
   Internet. By January, 2002, nearly 2,500 attorneys from over 800 firms
   had electronically filed over 218,000 documents in this Courts Maritime
   Asbestos and CM/ECF electronic filing systems. The Court strongly
   encourages attorneys to file documents electronically.
   [clearpixel.gif]
                    [Line.gif]
   [clearpixel.gif] [clearpixel.gif]

   NOTE: CM/ECF Users Must Have Obtained a PACER Account by June 18, 2001
   - Recent enhancements to the Courts CM/ECF system now require that
   users have a PACER account in addition to their CM/ECF identification
   name and password to access documents.
   For full details click here.
   The United States District Court for the Northern District of Ohio
   hereby orders that, absent a showing of good cause, all documents,
   notices and orders in all social security reviews filed in this
   district on or after January 1, 2001 shall be filed and noticed
   electronically, rather than on paper.
   For full details click here.
   The Court will be presenting seminars to provide attorneys and their
   staffs with the knowledge necessary to use the electronic filing
   system.
   Click here to read more and for scheduled dates and times.

   Beginning July 1st , 2000, all new civil cases filed in the United
   States District Court for the Northern District of Ohio will be placed
   in the Case Management/Electronic Case Filing CM/ECF system.
   For full details click here.

